The course will begin with the introduction to ethics and professional ethics. The questions about what is professionality and what does society expect of teacher and why, will be touched. Through the discussions of the problem cases in ethics of teaching, the main theories of ethics will be introduced, the question about what are our values and what questions will be raised through conflicts of values are studied, the regulatory documents and codes of ethics of teaching will be acquainted. In the concluding seminar the methods of making moral judgements will be thought about.Objectives/eesmärkid:  Raising the awareness of the ethical aspects of pedagogical work.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  The students will: 1) have good knowledge of the most basic theories and concepts in ethics, which are used in analysing the cases; 2) be familiar with the general issues of professional ethics; with the aims of codes of ethics; and with teachers' code of ethics; 3) be aware of their own moral beliefs and values, of the sources of these, and are able to evaluate them critically; 4) be aware of the society's expectations and demands for teachers; 5) be aware of the ethical problems arising in teaching, will be able to discuss them systematically and thoughtfully and hence to move towards the solutions.
